P \in \mathbb{Z}[x], P = \displaystyle\sum_{j=0}^n a_j x^j
a_0 \neq 0
a_n \neq 0
P(p/q)=0, p\perp q
p|a_0
q|a_n
r_j
a_0 = a_n \displaystyle\prod_{j=1}^n (-r_j)
a_0 = a_n \frac{-p}{q} \displaystyle\prod_{j=2}^n (-r_j)
a_n = q\frac{a_0}{-p \displaystyle\prod_{j=2}^n (-r_j)}
\frac{a_0}{-p \displaystyle\prod_{j=2}^n (-r_j)} \in \mathbb{Z}
a_0 = k(-p)\displaystyle\prod_{j=2}^n (-r_j) + \epsilon
\epsilon \in (0, (-p)\displaystyle\prod_{j=2}^n (-r_j))
